        <num>CC 2766</num>
        <heading>2766.  Termination of contract by death of workman</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2766.  Termination of contract by death of workman.
Contracts for hiring out work are canceled by the death of the workman, architect or undertaker, unless the proprietor should consent that the work should be continued by the heir or heirs of the architect, or by workmen employed for that purpose by the heirs.</p>
        </content>
